/*
Basic Commands
    1.Create package.json - npm init
    2.Create packge.json - 
        intsall Express - npm i express

Basic Steps
    1.creating a folder - (bankserver)
    2.create a package.json file - (npm init)
    3.create a nodemodules file (npm express)
    4.create Index.js file 
    5.import express into index.js
        const express = require("express");
    6.create app using express
        const app = express();
    7.set up port number
        app.listen(3000,()=>{
            console.log('listenig on port 3000');
        })
    8.resolving http requests
        app.get('/', (req, res) => {
            res.send('Get http request');
        })
    9.Install nodemon - npm i -g nodemon
    10.To get json file in javascript
        app.use(express.json());

    11.Http respose code
        1xx - Information
        2xx - successfull
        3xx - redirection
        4xx - client error
        5xx - server error

    12. JWT Token - Authentication
        In simple term, Authentication is the process of verifying who a user is, while authorizationn is the 
        process of verifying what they have access to.

        To check login or not?
            login -> token generate -> client -> req to deposit + token -> server token check?
        Install JWT Token - json webtoken
            npm i json webtoken
        To generate a new JWT Token - sign()

    13. Middleware - To verify the token    
        it comes in the middle of the request and response
        it also provide access to many function

        1. Application level Middleware
            For entire application
        2.Rounter level Middleware
            To verify token
            To validate token - verify()     

    14.Database integration                 
        Install mongoose - for connecting nodejs and mongodb (npm i mongoose)
        Db connect via mongoose
        Create a model using mongoose

    15.Asychronous Function Resolving
        1.Resolving State - then()
        2.Rejection State - catch()

    16. CORS - Cross origin resource sharing
        install cors - npm i cores



*/        